The paper presents an algorithm for computing minimum cycle bases in weighted partial 2-trees, which involves graph theory and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are likely sub-categories. The paper also involves optimization and complexity analysis, which suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as possible sub-categories.
